# Lab build — local preview

When you modify files under `templates/lab-build/` (or `public/lab-build/`), **end the response with the local preview block** so the user can review in the browser.

## Sync (source → preview)

From repo root:

```bash
python3 scripts/sync-lab-build-preview.py
# or: npm run sync:lab-build
```

`npm run serve` runs this sync automatically before starting the static server.

## Preview URLs

| File | URL |
|------|-----|
| `cli-lab-build-intake.html` | http://localhost:3000/lab-build/cli-lab-build-intake.html |
| `cli-lab-realistic.html` | http://localhost:3000/lab-build/cli-lab-realistic.html |

Hard refresh: **Cmd+Shift+R** (Mac) or **Ctrl+Shift+R** (Windows).

Do not place lab-build authoring pages under `public/CCNA-Study/` — use `public/lab-build/` only for localhost preview copies.
